trend_summary: Forested terrain is gradually opened for agriculture, quarrying and dispersed housing. Built-up footprint grows slowly but remains scattered along new and widened roads, while forest cover shrinks, especially centrally. A quarry enlarges and several curvilinear subdivisions appear near the southeast. The landscape stays predominantly rural with sparse overall density.
notable_changes: Progressive forest thinning and patch fragmentation in central–northern zones.
Marked enlargement of an open-pit quarry in the east.
Emergence of a new curvilinear residential subdivision in the southeast corner.
Conversion of woodland to agricultural fields in the northwest.
Upgrading and straightening of an east–west arterial road corridor.
